result.execSummary:
The defendant Warren Keith Vanzile was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Warren Keith Vanzile is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Warren Keith Vanzile was found guilty of Negligent Operation of Motor Vehicle, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Warren Keith Vanzile in court with attorney Steven Michael Lucareli.  Defendant Warren Keith Vanzile in custody and appears via video from Kettle Morraine Correctional Facility.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:09 AM. Court - believes the matter is settled and no need for motion hearing. state and Lucareli agree. State - amend #1 to negligent operation of a motor vehicle contrary to 941.01(1) - class A misd, dismiss #2 and #3, have complied with victim notification requirements with no response from victim (A.B.) - defendant would plead g/nc to amended count with joint recommendation of 9 months of incarceration. Lucarelli interrupts and states that the sentence is to be concurrent to his current sentence that he is now serving with a release date of 10/18/2016. State agrees. Court makes statement, what case is it to be concurrent to. Vanzile responds that it is a Forest County Case. Court does extensive verbal collaquey with the defendant on his right to go forth with the PLEAS via video and not in person. Vanzile understands and agrees to concluding the case today with a PLEAS via video. Court amends count #1 to negligent operation of a motor vehicle contrary to 941.01(1). Court has plea questionnaire. Vanzile pleads NC to amended count #1. Court dismisses counts #2 and #3. Court goes thru plea questionnaire, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights and right to JT, Court accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - again reiterates that the State has complied with victim notification requirements - follow joint recommendation. Lucareli makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Vanzile makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - 6 months in FC jail - concurrent to time he is now serving on Forest County Case #09CF14, costs - paid 60 days after release from incarceration/CO (10/18/16), submit DNA sample, right to appeal, address right now is c/o Kettle Morraine Correctional Institute, P.O.Box 282, Inmate #493855, Plymouth, WI  53073 and then c/o Keith Vanzile, 10804 Sokaogon Drive, Crandon, Wi  54520, adjourned at 11:43 AM.
